descriptionMarkdown:
Inputs on top pole: Red wire is current amount, Green wire is target, Each Top Red Wire/Each Top Green Wire= Each Bottom Red Wire. Targets may be set on internal P combinator, or sent in on top pole green wire from anywhere. Output on bottom pole is fraction of P: Each Bottom pole Red Wire/P = Percent full. Because Factorio cannot handle decimal numbers; you may set precision with P. 

1k/1200 = 1

10k/1200= 8

100k/1200=83

Resulting in one decimal more precision with each increasing power of 10 for P: P should be of the same magnitude (power of 10 for largest digit) as your largest green input, or larger. It is suggested to use a power of 10 to make conversion of output values into percent easier, as you need only shift the decimal point. Output value 4,000 with P=10,000 is equivalent to 0.4.
title: Red Each/Green Each
